5|$|The Victorian media portrayed Franklin {{as a hero}} {{despite the}} expedition's failure and the reports of cannibalism. Songs were written about him, and statues of him in his home town, in London, and in Tasmania credit him with {{discovery}} of the Northwest Passage which was actually found by John Rae. Franklin's lost expedition {{has been the subject}} of many artistic works, including songs, verse, <b>short</b> <b>stories,</b> <b>and</b> novels, as well as television documentaries.|$|E
