5|$|A {{total of}} sixty-nine poems, sixty <b>short</b> <b>stories,</b> <b>and</b> three serials were {{published}} in Asia Raya, a newspaper in the Dutch East Indies and early Indonesia. First published on 29 April 1942, months after the Empire of Japan invaded the Indies, Asia Raya was established under the occupation government and intended {{as a vehicle for}} pro-Japanese propaganda– including literature. Run by both Japanese and native staff, the newspaper remained in publication until 7September 1945, closing {{less than a month after}} Indonesia proclaimed its independence.|$|E
